# High-Performance Game Server Checkpoint | Walkthrough

This walkthrough outlines the implementations created for the Clash Of Kings style high-performance distributed game server architecture.

## Overview

The setup strictly adheres to a **No-Ask Policy** utilizing **Pekko's Cluster Sharding** and **Event Sourced Behaviors** natively with Java 21 `Records`. 

### Key Deliverables Completed:
1. **Java 21 Project Initialized:** We configured [pom.xml](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/pom.xml) with Pekko 1.0.3 and all the necessary persistence and sharding libraries. I also upgraded the host JDK explicitly to Java 21 via SDKMAN to ensure Maven compiled the code correctly using `<source>21</source>`.
2. **Core Domain Models:** Introduced immutable Data `Records`: [PlayerProfileAggregate](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/models/PlayerProfileAggregate.java#7-22), [BuildingMirror](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/models/BuildingMirror.java#5-6), [BuildingState](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/models/BuildingState.java#5-11), and base marker interface [JsonSerializable](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/protocol/JsonSerializable.java#6-7). 
3. **No-Ask Master-Slave Architecture:**
   - **[Master Actor] KingdomPlayerActor:** Built `EventSourcedBehavior` logic handling commands from simple proxies, validating state securely through `BuildingDomainService.canUpgrade`, and passing immutable commands via `tell()` to corresponding Slave shards.
   - **[Slave Actor] BuildingActor:** Processes commands, performs database commits (simulate using `jdbc-journal`), and only *after* a successful commit explicitly performs a Push update `replyToMaster.tell(BuildingUpdateNotification...)` using a generic payload, safely maintaining an Eventual Consistent mirror.
4. **Bootstrapping Script:** Added [Main.java](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/Main.java) which boots the "ConquererSystem" Actor System, initializes the Sharding module to securely hold state, and tests an instantiation query via [UpgradeBuildingCmd("Castle", "MAIN_CASTLE")](file:///home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2/src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/protocol/UpgradeBuildingCmd.java#3-5).

## Successful Validation

The code gracefully compiles without warnings under `javac release 21`:

```
